  <section class="hero">
    <h1>Frequently Asked Questions</h1>
    <p>Everything customers usually want to know before booking a jet ski or boat rental.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="section">

    <div class="notice">
      Final requirements, pricing, availability, and safety instructions are confirmed during booking and check-in.
      Lake conditions, weather, and local rules may affect rentals.
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <h2>How do I book a rental?</h2>
      <p>Use the online booking section on our homepage to check availability, select a time, and reserve your rental.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <h2>Can I pay online?</h2>
      <p>Yes. Online booking allows customers to reserve and pay through the booking system when required.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <h2>Do I need to call first?</h2>
      <p>No. The easiest way is to book online. You can still call or text if you have a specific question before booking.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <h2>Where are you located?</h2>
      <p>We serve Chicago’s lakefront. Exact meeting details are provided after booking or confirmation.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <h2>What are your hours?</h2>
      <p>Hours vary by season, weather, and availability. The booking calendar will show available times.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <h2>What happens if the weather is bad?</h2>
      <p>Safety comes first. If lake or weather conditions are unsafe, the rental may need to be rescheduled.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <h2>Do I need experience to rent a jet ski?</h2>
      <p>Basic instructions are provided before riding. Renters should feel comfortable following safety directions and operating responsibly.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <h2>Do I need a boating license or safety certificate?</h2>
      <p>Requirements can depend on the rental type, operator age, and local/state rules. Any required safety or operator rules will be confirmed before the rental.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <h2>Are life jackets provided?</h2>
      <p>Life jackets or personal flotation devices are part of safe water activity. Proper safety equipment requirements will be reviewed before riding.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <h2>What should I bring?</h2>
      <p>Bring a valid ID, payment method if needed, sunscreen, towel, water-friendly clothing, and anything you need to be comfortable on the lakefront.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <h2>Can I bring my phone?</h2>
      <p>You can, but water damage is always a risk. A waterproof pouch is recommended if you plan to bring your phone near the water.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <h2>Can multiple people ride?</h2>
      <p>Passenger limits depend on the rental type, equipment, safety rules, and weight limits. Details are confirmed before the rental.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <h2>Can I drink alcohol before or during the rental?</h2>
      <p>No. Customers should not operate any watercraft while under the influence. Safety rules must be followed at all times.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <h2>What if I’m late?</h2>
      <p>Please arrive on time. Late arrival may reduce your rental time because other bookings may be scheduled after yours.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <h2>Is there a security deposit?</h2>
      <p>Deposit requirements may vary depending on the rental. Any deposit or damage policy will be shown or explained before confirmation.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <h2>What is the cancellation policy?</h2>
      <p>Cancellation and rescheduling rules may vary by booking type, weather, and timing. Check your booking confirmation for details.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <h2>Can I book for a group or event?</h2>
      <p>Yes, depending on availability. For groups, birthdays, or special requests, call or text before booking.</p>
    </div>

  </section>

  <section class="cta">
    <h2>Still Have Questions?</h2>
    <p>Call or text us, or check availability online.</p>
